BFN 

  [Text] Today in Kiev, the Ukrainian-Chinese 
Intergovernmental Commission for Trade and Economic Cooperation 
held its first meeting. As Deputy Prime Minister Valeriy 
Shmarov, head of the Ukrainian half of the commission, noted, 
the body is supposed to establish new bases for developing 
bilateral trade and economic relations, as well as define the 
primary direction of cooperation. In the opinion of Valeriy 
Shmarov, the annual volume of trade between Ukraine and China 
could reach a level of $4 billion. Last year, it amounted to 
$670 million, with Ukrainian exports totalling $580 million. 

